main event: A round, glowing object, about 6-8 times the size of a star, was observed in the sky near Omaha, Nebraska, on January 9, 1950.
interesting points: The object had a brilliant white light in the center with dimmer lights on each side., The observation lasted for 15 minutes., The description of the object was characteristic of a star, but the reported temperature and magnitude did not match., The observer was looking out of his kitchen window with binoculars., The object was noted to twinkle, and its movement was reported to be westerly with increasing altitude.
sighted object: a round, glowing object with brilliant white light
witness description: The observer used a pair of binoculars to observe the object.
